main event: Multiple reports of unidentified aerial objects observed in Trenton, N.J. between July 7 and July 29, 1952.
interesting points: Witnesses reported seeing round, luminous objects with a diameter of approximately 30 feet,Observed that the objects emitted a blue-white glow and were capable of high-speed acceleration,Reports indicated that similar sightings have been frequent in the Trenton area since July 1952,The objects were described as moving in an erratic manner and could not be identified as any known aircraft,Investigators noted the reliability of witnesses as undetermined, but with ongoing investigations.
witness description: Civilians in the Trenton area, including residents and army pickets
